The paper discusses deep hashing methods for content-based image retrieval, which involves computer vision (CV) and information retrieval (IR) techniques. Therefore, cs.CV and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also evaluates the performance of deep hashing methods using experimental results, which involves machine learning (LG) and multimedia (MM) techniques. Additionally, the paper discusses the flaws in the evaluation criteria of existing deep hashing papers, which involves artificial intelligence (AI) techniques.
